com.linkedin.parseq.function

Interface Try<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Failure, Success

    public interface Try<T>
    The Try interface represents result that may either be a successful completion or a failure. It has two implementation: Success and Failure. New instances of Try can be created by either calling Success.of(...) of Failure.of(...).
    Author:
    Jaroslaw Odzga (jodzga@linkedin.com)
    See Also:
    Success, Failure
